      • createResource

        public static IMediaResource createResource(IMediaFolder parent,
                                            java.io.File f)
        createResource() is used as a factory for Filesystem File objects to ensure that a Filesystem File, such as a DVD or bluray disc gets created as the correct type of IMediaResource.

        FileMediaFile or FileMediaFolder should now be created directly but rather they should only be created when using this factory.

        Parameters:
        -
        Returns:

      • resolveBluRay

        public static java.io.File resolveBluRay(java.io.File f)
        resolveBluRay() attempt to resolve a file as a BluRay folder. It will return the path of the BDMV folder or a parent folder that contains a .m2ts file.
        Parameters:

      • resolveDVD

        public static java.io.File resolveDVD(java.io.File f)
        resolveDVD() attempts to resolve a DVD file by inspecting the file to see if it a dvd file. If it is a dvd file, then it will return it as a directory of either the VIDEO_TS dir or a dir that contains a .vob file.
        Parameters:
        f -
